WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.026 --> 00:00:06.157
Hold it.

2
00:00:06.288 --> 00:00:07.854
It's OK.

3
00:00:07.985 --> 00:00:09.639
The airline has literally
never had a single accident

4
00:00:09.769 --> 00:00:11.119
in its entire existence.

5
00:00:11.249 --> 00:00:13.077
Sorry.
husband's a nervous flyer.

6
00:00:13.208 --> 00:00:15.166
Good night.

7
00:00:15.297 --> 00:00:17.168
Just breathe. Abdullah.

8
00:00:17.299 --> 00:00:19.475
Find something to hold
with both hands.

9
00:00:19.605 --> 00:00:21.216
[siren wailing]

10
00:00:21.346 --> 00:00:22.913
That's OK.

11
00:00:23.044 --> 00:00:25.524
No. the... the seat you have
is better anyway.

12
00:00:25.655 --> 00:00:28.266
<i>[ominous music]</i>

13
00:00:28.397 --> 00:00:29.615
You know what'll help?

14
00:00:29.746 --> 00:00:31.182
Honey. you're fine.

15
00:00:31.313 --> 00:00:32.836
Try to use headphones.

16
00:00:32.966 --> 00:00:35.534
Ask the flight attendant...
[shouts]

17
00:00:35.665 --> 00:00:37.884
[screaming]

18
00:00:38.015 --> 00:00:46.015
<i>♪</i>

19
00:00:50.332 --> 00:00:52.160
So how many more days
is Ramadan?

20
00:00:52.290 --> 00:00:54.336
Uh. including today.
28 more days.

21
00:00:54.466 --> 00:00:56.425
Oof. a month without coffee.

22
00:00:56.555 --> 00:00:59.080
Well. I can have it
when the sun goes down.

23
00:00:59.210 --> 00:01:00.733
if I don't want to sleep.

24
00:01:00.864 --> 00:01:02.518
But other than that. just no
food or drink during the day.

25
00:01:02.648 --> 00:01:03.693
It's easy.

26
00:01:03.823 --> 00:01:05.303
Why are you observing now?

27
00:01:05.434 --> 00:01:07.044
You haven't the whole time
I've known you.

28
00:01:07.175 --> 00:01:08.176
I don't know.

29
00:01:08.306 --> 00:01:09.177
After Gemma and I broke up.

30
00:01:09.307 --> 00:01:10.569
I started meditating again.

31
00:01:10.700 --> 00:01:12.528
And fasting is a form
of meditation.

32
00:01:12.658 --> 00:01:14.834
It lowers the volume on
everything so I can think.

33
00:01:14.965 --> 00:01:17.098
About how hungry you are?

34
00:01:17.228 --> 00:01:18.229
Hey. Sal.

35
00:01:18.360 --> 00:01:19.839
Hey. Maggie.

36
00:01:19.970 --> 00:01:22.233
Can I get my coffee and
cinnamon raisin bagel today?

37
00:01:22.364 --> 00:01:23.974
$20.

38
00:01:24.105 --> 00:01:25.541
That's steep.

39
00:01:25.671 --> 00:01:27.064
I've been robbed twice
in the past month.

40
00:01:27.195 --> 00:01:29.284
first in Brownsville
and then here.

41
00:01:29.414 --> 00:01:31.068
They swiped the register
while I was throwing out

42
00:01:31.199 --> 00:01:32.287
the coffee grinds.

43
00:01:32.417 --> 00:01:34.724
[phone buzzing]
- I'm sorry to hear that.

44
00:01:34.854 --> 00:01:36.682
Are you gonna... you got it.

45
00:01:36.813 --> 00:01:37.727
Hey.

46
00:01:37.857 --> 00:01:39.250
Did you call the cops?

47
00:01:39.381 --> 00:01:40.512
Yeah. a lot of good
that did me. right?

48
00:01:40.643 --> 00:01:42.079
Yeah. I hear you.

49
00:01:42.210 --> 00:01:44.777
OK.

50
00:01:44.908 --> 00:01:47.998
OK. Keep us posted.
[phone beeps]

51
00:01:48.129 --> 00:01:50.087
There was a body dumped under
the LIE. federal employee.

52
00:01:50.218 --> 00:01:52.133
Scola and Eva are headed
over there now.

53
00:01:52.263 --> 00:01:54.265
Thank you.
- OK.

54
00:01:54.396 --> 00:01:55.745
Hey.

55
00:01:55.875 --> 00:01:57.094
Sorry for running late.

56
00:01:57.225 --> 00:01:58.443
Just talked to NYPD.

57
00:01:58.574 --> 00:02:01.925
Sanitation worker found
a body around 6:00 AM.

58
00:02:02.055 --> 00:02:05.233
Medical ID badge says
she's a doctor.

59
00:02:05.363 --> 00:02:08.323
Saima Khan. psychiatrist
at the Southport VA.

60
00:02:08.453 --> 00:02:09.585
Southport?

61
00:02:09.715 --> 00:02:11.326
That's one of the
busiest VAs in New York.

62
00:02:11.456 --> 00:02:13.415
Unless you're there
three hours after they closed.

63
00:02:13.545 --> 00:02:15.765
She left around 9:00.
never made it to her car.

64
00:02:15.895 --> 00:02:17.462
She parked
less than a block away.

65
00:02:17.593 --> 00:02:19.551
Couldn't have been more
than a minute's walk.

66
00:02:19.682 --> 00:02:21.031
No cameras?

67
00:02:21.162 --> 00:02:24.034
No cameras.

68
00:02:24.165 --> 00:02:25.818
Well. we got a shot to the head.

69
00:02:25.949 --> 00:02:27.298
and then this type of bruising

70
00:02:27.429 --> 00:02:30.432
suggests the other impacts
were at least four hours

71
00:02:30.562 --> 00:02:32.042
earlier before she was shot.

72
00:02:32.173 --> 00:02:33.304
There's more.

73
00:02:33.435 --> 00:02:35.088
See this hand?

74
00:02:35.219 --> 00:02:37.221
<i>[tense music]</i>

75
00:02:37.352 --> 00:02:38.570
Yeah. it's been burned.

76
00:02:38.701 --> 00:02:40.790
I don't know if
that's knowledge of pain points

77
00:02:40.920 --> 00:02:43.184
or what. but whoever did this

78
00:02:43.314 --> 00:02:46.448
wanted to inflict
maximum suffering.

79
00:02:46.578 --> 00:02:48.276
So they abducted her
from outside her work.

80
00:02:48.406 --> 00:02:50.408
they tortured her all night.

81
00:02:50.539 --> 00:02:54.238
and then they killed her.
and they dumped her here.

82
00:02:54.369 --> 00:02:57.241
Someone had it out for her
in a bad way.

83
00:02:57.372 --> 00:02:59.156
[indistinct shouting]

84
00:02:59.287 --> 00:03:00.853
Please. Saima!

85
00:03:00.984 --> 00:03:03.421
No. no!
Please! Please!

86
00:03:03.552 --> 00:03:05.118
No!

87
00:03:05.249 --> 00:03:07.077
Saima! Please!

88
00:03:07.208 --> 00:03:10.472
Please!

89
00:03:10.602 --> 00:03:12.909
I hate this part.

90
00:03:13.039 --> 00:03:15.651
Mr. Khan. we're gonna do
everything we can

91
00:03:15.781 --> 00:03:17.479
to find out the person
who did this. OK?

92
00:03:17.609 --> 00:03:19.350
Why won't you let me see her?

93
00:03:19.481 --> 00:03:21.439
We're still processing
the scene right now.

94
00:03:21.570 --> 00:03:23.093
And to be honest with you.

95
00:03:23.224 --> 00:03:24.660
you don't want to see her
like this.

96
00:03:24.790 --> 00:03:26.444
- [groans]
- Were you able to hear

97
00:03:26.575 --> 00:03:28.141
any other voice on the phone?

98
00:03:28.272 --> 00:03:31.710
No. not a word.
just her screaming.

99
00:03:31.841 --> 00:03:34.278
After that.
I-I heard a car drive off.

100
00:03:34.409 --> 00:03:36.324
But my connection dropped
when the plane started moving.

101
00:03:36.454 --> 00:03:38.108
Can you think of anyone
that might have wanted

102
00:03:38.239 --> 00:03:39.283
to hurt your wife?

103
00:03:39.414 --> 00:03:40.371
None of this would have happened

104
00:03:40.502 --> 00:03:42.808
if the VA just listened to us.

105
00:03:42.939 --> 00:03:43.853
We told them he would come back.

106
00:03:43.983 --> 00:03:45.376
He's obsessed with her.

107
00:03:45.507 --> 00:03:48.727
You told them
who would come back?

108
00:03:48.858 --> 00:03:51.687
All right. folks. so last
night. a VA psychiatrist.

109
00:03:51.817 --> 00:03:54.646
Dr. Saima Kahn. was abducted

110
00:03:54.777 --> 00:03:56.387
and then found dead
this morning.

111
00:03:56.518 --> 00:03:57.693
Six years with the VA.

112
00:03:57.823 --> 00:03:59.085
According to the head
of the department.

113
00:03:59.216 --> 00:04:02.393
she was as good as they come...
devoted. caring.

114
00:04:02.524 --> 00:04:04.526
Anyway. her husband tipped us
off to a former patient

115
00:04:04.656 --> 00:04:06.528
as a suspect. Luke Williams.

116
00:04:06.658 --> 00:04:07.964
Yeah. What do we got on him?

117
00:04:08.094 --> 00:04:10.445
Combat medic.
did two tours in Afghanistan.

118
00:04:10.575 --> 00:04:13.970
Three months ago. Dr. Khan put
Williams in an involuntary hold

119
00:04:14.100 --> 00:04:16.146
for severe PTSD with
secondary psychosis

120
00:04:16.277 --> 00:04:18.279
after he confessed
to her in therapy

121
00:04:18.409 --> 00:04:20.629
that he almost strangled his
roommate during a night terror.

122
00:04:20.759 --> 00:04:22.326
OK. so she used his confession

123
00:04:22.457 --> 00:04:23.719
to have him committed.

124
00:04:23.849 --> 00:04:25.547
I'm sure that upset him.
but I don't know.

125
00:04:25.677 --> 00:04:27.157
enough to kill the good doctor?

126
00:04:27.288 --> 00:04:28.985
After the 72-hour hold.
Khan asked the court

127
00:04:29.115 --> 00:04:31.335
to extend it for 60 days.

128
00:04:31.466 --> 00:04:34.077
When Williams was released.
he lost his job.

129
00:04:34.207 --> 00:04:36.122
Uh. there's no record
of any new leases.

130
00:04:36.253 --> 00:04:37.733
probably couldn't afford
to sign one.

131
00:04:37.863 --> 00:04:39.212
Which would make him unhoused.

132
00:04:39.343 --> 00:04:41.867
And he blames Khan
for the loss of his livelihood.

133
00:04:41.998 --> 00:04:43.565
definitely enough for motive.

134
00:04:43.695 --> 00:04:45.001
Cameras show Williams kept
showing up at the hospital.

135
00:04:45.131 --> 00:04:46.742
demanding to see Dr. Khan.

136
00:04:46.872 --> 00:04:51.790
O-OK. so he was looking for
a chance to confront her.

137
00:04:51.921 --> 00:04:53.488
Williams has a gun
registered to him

138
00:04:53.618 --> 00:04:55.490
that matches the caliber
of the murder weapon.

139
00:04:55.620 --> 00:04:57.753
It was set to be confiscated
during his psych hold

140
00:04:57.883 --> 00:04:59.929
under the New York CARE Act.
but they've been backlogged.

141
00:05:00.059 --> 00:05:01.322
Where's Williams now?

142
00:05:01.452 --> 00:05:03.498
His phone is pinging
East Brooklyn.

143
00:05:03.628 --> 00:05:06.457
<i>[tense music]</i>

144
00:05:06.588 --> 00:05:09.591
<i>♪</i>

145
00:05:09.721 --> 00:05:10.853
Look. Scola. there he is.

146
00:05:10.983 --> 00:05:12.681
- Luke Williams. FBI.
We need a word.

147
00:05:12.811 --> 00:05:14.247
- What do you want?
I'm eating.

148
00:05:14.378 --> 00:05:15.553
We just want to ask you
a few questions. all right?

149
00:05:15.684 --> 00:05:16.554
Can you come with us?

150
00:05:16.685 --> 00:05:17.773
No.

151
00:05:17.903 --> 00:05:20.253
No. I'm not going with you.

152
00:05:20.384 --> 00:05:21.777
I'm not going.

153
00:05:21.907 --> 00:05:24.040
- Gun. Hey! Hey.
Up against the wall.

154
00:05:24.170 --> 00:05:26.347
[shouts] Assault!

155
00:05:26.477 --> 00:05:27.565
- Hands behind your back.
- Police brutality!

156
00:05:27.696 --> 00:05:29.001
Police brutality!

157
00:05:29.132 --> 00:05:30.133
- You're hurting him.
What did he do?

158
00:05:30.263 --> 00:05:31.439
Ma'am. please step back.

159
00:05:31.569 --> 00:05:32.265
He was just sitting here.

160
00:05:32.396 --> 00:05:33.789
You gonna grab him like that?

161
00:05:33.919 --> 00:05:35.399
Ma'am. this is for your safety.

162
00:05:35.530 --> 00:05:36.922
Please. step back. ma'am.

163
00:05:37.053 --> 00:05:38.402
Yeah. I'm recording.

164
00:05:38.533 --> 00:05:39.838
We're recording.

165
00:05:39.969 --> 00:05:42.406
Now. come on. This ain't right.

166
00:05:42.537 --> 00:05:44.103
It ain't right.

167
00:05:44.234 --> 00:05:46.323
You had a 9-millimeter pistol
in your possession.

168
00:05:46.454 --> 00:05:47.846
Mr. Williams.

169
00:05:47.977 --> 00:05:50.066
Concealed carry is illegal
in New York

170
00:05:50.196 --> 00:05:52.155
without a pistol license.
which you don't have.

171
00:05:52.285 --> 00:05:54.070
I don't got anywhere else
to keep it.

172
00:05:54.200 --> 00:05:55.767
Where were you last night
at 9:00 PM?

173
00:05:55.898 --> 00:05:57.552
I can't remember.

174
00:05:57.682 --> 00:05:59.380
A judge is not going to
accept that as an answer.

175
00:05:59.510 --> 00:06:01.773
So you might want to try
a little harder.

176
00:06:01.904 --> 00:06:04.820
This is me trying. man.

177
00:06:04.950 --> 00:06:07.431
My PTSD's got me all mixed up.

178
00:06:07.562 --> 00:06:11.696
I remember a screeching tire
set me off

179
00:06:11.827 --> 00:06:14.003
with a whopping migraine. where
I could barely walk straight.

180
00:06:14.133 --> 00:06:15.918
So I go. OK. time for the pills.

181
00:06:16.048 --> 00:06:18.181
But they're not
exactly cotton candy.

182
00:06:18.311 --> 00:06:19.878
Next thing I know.
I'm three stops down.

183
00:06:20.009 --> 00:06:21.880
no clue how I got there.

184
00:06:22.011 --> 00:06:24.187
Look. I know a lot of guys
that have been where you are.

185
00:06:24.317 --> 00:06:26.450
But you are gonna need to try
and point to someone

186
00:06:26.581 --> 00:06:28.670
who can tell us where you were
at 9:00 PM last night.

187
00:06:28.800 --> 00:06:30.846
a bartender. a landlord. something.

188
00:06:30.976 --> 00:06:33.979
Well. I don't have anyone.

189
00:06:34.110 --> 00:06:35.894
just my shrink. Dr. Khan.

190
00:06:36.025 --> 00:06:38.288
Until she stopped feeling
safe being your psychiatrist.

191
00:06:38.419 --> 00:06:39.855
That's not true.

192
00:06:39.985 --> 00:06:41.465
She stopped being my doctor

193
00:06:41.596 --> 00:06:44.512
because we're gonna be together.

194
00:06:44.642 --> 00:06:48.080
She's getting divorced. too.

195
00:06:48.211 --> 00:06:51.301
How are you gonna be together
if she's dead?

196
00:06:51.432 --> 00:06:54.826
She's...

197
00:06:54.957 --> 00:06:56.175
She's dead?

198
00:06:56.306 --> 00:06:57.873
Here's what I think happened.

199
00:06:58.003 --> 00:07:01.050
I think you mistook the therapy
that Dr. Khan gave you

200
00:07:01.180 --> 00:07:04.357
for an emotional connection
that you didn't actually have.

201
00:07:04.488 --> 00:07:06.490
And when you were forced
to confront that reality.

202
00:07:06.621 --> 00:07:07.796
you lost control.

203
00:07:07.926 --> 00:07:09.711
[scoffs]

204
00:07:09.841 --> 00:07:11.756
You think that I killed her?

205
00:07:11.887 --> 00:07:14.498
Dr. Khan was tortured in
a way to inflict maximum pain

206
00:07:14.629 --> 00:07:16.021
before she was killed.

207
00:07:16.152 --> 00:07:17.327
That is knowledge that you
would have as a field medic.

208
00:07:17.458 --> 00:07:19.155
I would never hurt Dr. Khan.

209
00:07:19.285 --> 00:07:21.549
You were removed multiple
times from the hospital.

210
00:07:21.679 --> 00:07:23.246
You tried to break in
to confront her

211
00:07:23.376 --> 00:07:24.856
after she put you
in an involuntary hold.

212
00:07:24.987 --> 00:07:26.336
It was after her therapy
that I could actually

213
00:07:26.467 --> 00:07:28.207
get some sleep.

214
00:07:28.338 --> 00:07:29.470
real sleep.

215
00:07:29.600 --> 00:07:31.297
Do you know how many shrinks
I've had?

216
00:07:31.428 --> 00:07:32.647
I mean. too freaking many.

217
00:07:32.777 --> 00:07:35.388
But Dr. Khan was different.

218
00:07:35.519 --> 00:07:36.781
We had a connection.

219
00:07:36.912 --> 00:07:38.479
I wouldn't ever hurt her.
I swear.

220
00:07:38.609 --> 00:07:40.481
If that was true. Luke.

221
00:07:40.611 --> 00:07:42.570
she would have told security
to let you in.

222
00:07:42.700 --> 00:07:45.529
It was the system
that kept us apart.

223
00:07:45.660 --> 00:07:50.360
I had to get creative if I was
going to tell her how I felt.

224
00:07:50.491 --> 00:07:51.753
That's it.

225
00:07:51.883 --> 00:07:54.973
That's where I was last night.
Brooks' Burgers.

226
00:07:55.104 --> 00:07:56.584
It's a restaurant
in Hell's Kitchen.

227
00:07:56.714 --> 00:07:58.281
It's her favorite spot.

228
00:07:58.411 --> 00:08:04.635
I was waiting there for her.
but she never showed.

229
00:08:04.766 --> 00:08:07.116
- Excuse me. FBI.
Special Agent Bell.

230
00:08:07.246 --> 00:08:09.248
This is Special Agent Zidan.

231
00:08:09.379 --> 00:08:11.599
Did you see this man
last night around 9:00 PM?

232
00:08:11.729 --> 00:08:12.991
Oh. yeah.

233
00:08:13.122 --> 00:08:14.993
That guy was in here
all night till closing.

234
00:08:15.124 --> 00:08:16.299
That booth over there.

235
00:08:16.429 --> 00:08:18.301
One cup of coffee.
only tipped $0.50.

236
00:08:18.431 --> 00:08:19.868
I mean. what am I gonna do
with that?

237
00:08:19.998 --> 00:08:22.131
Was he with this woman?

238
00:08:22.261 --> 00:08:23.567
Uh. he said this was her
favorite restaurant.

239
00:08:23.698 --> 00:08:24.829
You recognize her?

240
00:08:24.960 --> 00:08:26.962
She's a regular. Sa...

241
00:08:27.092 --> 00:08:28.311
Saima. right?
- Mm-hmm.

242
00:08:28.441 --> 00:08:29.399
She wasn't here last night.

243
00:08:29.530 --> 00:08:31.488
But I did see her in here
two days ago

244
00:08:31.619 --> 00:08:32.750
for lunch with some guy.

245
00:08:32.881 --> 00:08:34.839
OK. was it with this guy.
her husband?

246
00:08:34.970 --> 00:08:36.406
No. not him.

247
00:08:36.537 --> 00:08:39.148
Look. what two adults do
is their own business.

248
00:08:39.278 --> 00:08:41.019
I am not trying
to jam anybody up.

249
00:08:41.150 --> 00:08:42.368
Uh. did they pay
with credit card?

250
00:08:42.499 --> 00:08:43.587
Mm-hmm.

251
00:08:43.718 --> 00:08:47.199
We're gonna need
to see that receipt.

252
00:08:47.330 --> 00:08:49.158
- Hey. Jubal?
- Yeah?

253
00:08:49.288 --> 00:08:49.941
We got a name off that
credit card receipt

254
00:08:50.072 --> 00:08:51.334
the diner sent over.

255
00:08:51.464 --> 00:08:53.423
Aziz Khalil. 44.

256
00:08:53.554 --> 00:08:55.512
He's an Imam down at
the North Brooklyn Mosque.

257
00:08:55.643 --> 00:08:57.340
Yeah. I've been digging into
the Imam on his socials.

258
00:08:57.470 --> 00:08:58.994
Uh. he's a bit of a celebrity

259
00:08:59.124 --> 00:09:00.038
in the New York Muslim
community.

260
00:09:00.169 --> 00:09:01.387
- Hey. Jubal?
- Yeah?

261
00:09:01.518 --> 00:09:02.693
North Brooklyn Mosque
has popped recently

262
00:09:02.824 --> 00:09:04.869
on several open
NYPD investigations.

263
00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:06.044
OK. what do you got?

264
00:09:06.175 --> 00:09:08.133
We got two missing
persons reports.

265
00:09:08.264 --> 00:09:09.744
both in the last six weeks.

266
00:09:09.874 --> 00:09:12.311
Both of them are women
who attend the mosque.

267
00:09:12.442 --> 00:09:15.140
Laila Dani and Yasmeen Hakeem.

268
00:09:15.271 --> 00:09:19.492
O-OK. so our Imam shares
a meal with our murder victim

269
00:09:19.623 --> 00:09:23.105
shortly before two of his
female congregants go missing.

270
00:09:23.235 --> 00:09:24.454
Let's see if we can
tighten that thread.

271
00:09:24.585 --> 00:09:25.803
Hold on.

272
00:09:25.934 --> 00:09:26.978
These women didn't
just attend the mosque.

273
00:09:27.109 --> 00:09:28.632
They were generous donors.

274
00:09:28.763 --> 00:09:30.112
Oh. yeah. big fans.

275
00:09:30.242 --> 00:09:30.982
And they weren't just fans
of the Imam.

276
00:09:31.113 --> 00:09:32.680
He was a fan of theirs.

277
00:09:32.810 --> 00:09:34.725
I ran their names through the
auto-generated transcripts

278
00:09:34.856 --> 00:09:36.727
of the Imam's YouTube sermons

279
00:09:36.858 --> 00:09:38.860
the week before Yasmeen
disappeared.

280
00:09:38.990 --> 00:09:41.906
"Thank you to Yasmeen Hakeem
for your generous donation

281
00:09:42.037 --> 00:09:43.299
"to the <i>Sadaqa</i> program.

282
00:09:43.429 --> 00:09:44.735
May Allah protect her."

283
00:09:44.866 --> 00:09:47.259
OK. so... so he knew
them both personally.

284
00:09:47.390 --> 00:09:48.739
He gave him a shout-out
in his sermons.

285
00:09:48.870 --> 00:09:51.655
But one murder and two
missing persons reports

286
00:09:51.786 --> 00:09:53.962
don't make a pattern.
- Eh. what if they did?

287
00:09:54.092 --> 00:09:55.485
According to our reports.
these women were last seen

288
00:09:55.616 --> 00:09:57.879
at work. disappeared at night.

289
00:09:58.009 --> 00:09:59.576
They haven't been seen since.

290
00:09:59.707 --> 00:10:01.186
The only difference between
this and Dr. Khan's case

291
00:10:01.317 --> 00:10:02.884
is we found her body.

292
00:10:03.014 --> 00:10:05.060
All right. let's get ERT back
to that crime scene

293
00:10:05.190 --> 00:10:06.931
under the overpass. see if
any other bodies turn up.

294
00:10:07.062 --> 00:10:10.152
If they do. we could be dealing
with a serial killer

295
00:10:10.282 --> 00:10:11.980
preying on women
in the Muslim community.

296
00:10:12.110 --> 00:10:15.636
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

297
00:10:21.293 --> 00:10:22.425
<i>We ask you to grant</i> maghfirah

298
00:10:22.555 --> 00:10:25.297
<i>on sister Laila Dani's mother.
Seema.</i>

299
00:10:25.428 --> 00:10:26.864
<i>who is in the hospital
right now.</i>

300
00:10:26.995 --> 00:10:28.126
<i>- [congregants]</i> Ameen!
- OK. yeah.

301
00:10:28.257 --> 00:10:29.737
that's a prayer called a <i>dua.</i>

302
00:10:29.867 --> 00:10:31.608
Bigger groups amplify the
chances of the prayer coming

303
00:10:31.739 --> 00:10:33.218
true. so the Imam
will give one of those

304
00:10:33.349 --> 00:10:34.785
at the end of every sermon.

305
00:10:34.916 --> 00:10:37.570
Now. he mentioned each
of our missing women.

306
00:10:37.701 --> 00:10:40.312
including Dr. Khan.

307
00:10:40.443 --> 00:10:42.097
but before they went missing.

308
00:10:42.227 --> 00:10:43.751
So what if he's choosing
the women

309
00:10:43.881 --> 00:10:45.230
in front of a live audience

310
00:10:45.361 --> 00:10:46.928
to make them feel special?

311
00:10:47.058 --> 00:10:48.712
Then he invites him in
for a one-on-one meeting

312
00:10:48.843 --> 00:10:50.192
where they're vulnerable.

313
00:10:50.322 --> 00:10:51.889
then goes in for the kill.

314
00:10:52.020 --> 00:10:54.109
I mean. it's possible. but he
did mention other women. too.

315
00:10:54.239 --> 00:10:55.545
and they're perfectly fine.

316
00:10:55.676 --> 00:10:57.547
Yeah. all... all our evidence
is circumstantial.

317
00:10:57.678 --> 00:10:59.854
OK. then. if we're gonna
take a swing at this guy.

318
00:10:59.984 --> 00:11:01.725
let's start by talking to
people that sit with him

319
00:11:01.856 --> 00:11:03.466
week in and week out
that know him.

320
00:11:03.596 --> 00:11:08.732
not this video
or his public persona.

321
00:11:08.863 --> 00:11:11.822
My sister was a hardcore
follower of Imam Aziz.

322
00:11:11.953 --> 00:11:14.216
She checked his
YouTube page daily.

323
00:11:14.346 --> 00:11:16.392
You're not as big a fan.
I take it?

324
00:11:16.522 --> 00:11:18.437
He put on a good front.

325
00:11:18.568 --> 00:11:20.570
But after
we reported her missing.

326
00:11:20.701 --> 00:11:23.138
her husband. Khaled.
went to the Imam.

327
00:11:23.268 --> 00:11:24.966
He wanted to make
an announcement

328
00:11:25.096 --> 00:11:26.968
after Friday's <i>Juma</i> prayer.

329
00:11:27.098 --> 00:11:28.186
ask if anyone had seen her.

330
00:11:28.317 --> 00:11:29.535
And the Imam refused?

331
00:11:29.666 --> 00:11:31.755
He said it was a police matter.

332
00:11:31.886 --> 00:11:33.888
It seemed strange.

333
00:11:34.018 --> 00:11:36.368
Why wouldn't he mention
Yasmeen by name?

334
00:11:36.499 --> 00:11:37.979
Khaled and I didn't understand.

335
00:11:38.109 --> 00:11:39.676
Why would he refuse?

336
00:11:39.807 --> 00:11:41.547
We're actually gonna talk
to her husband tomorrow.

337
00:11:41.678 --> 00:11:43.027
when he gets back into town.

338
00:11:43.158 --> 00:11:45.116
He's been looking for
a private investigator

339
00:11:45.247 --> 00:11:46.465
that can help us.

340
00:11:46.596 --> 00:11:50.339
The police are not doing enough.

341
00:11:50.469 --> 00:11:54.125
This has devastated my family.

342
00:11:54.256 --> 00:11:56.911
every hour.

343
00:11:57.041 --> 00:11:59.696
living with the terror of
not knowing what's happened.

344
00:11:59.827 --> 00:12:02.220
Ms. Hakeem.
do you know if your sister

345
00:12:02.351 --> 00:12:04.222
had any sort of a. um.

346
00:12:04.353 --> 00:12:06.921
more intense relationship
with the Imam?

347
00:12:07.051 --> 00:12:09.271
I've been suspicious
ever since she told me

348
00:12:09.401 --> 00:12:12.056
about this weekly women's-only
Halaqa he's been running.

349
00:12:12.187 --> 00:12:15.233
It's a Islamic study group.
no men allowed.

350
00:12:15.364 --> 00:12:17.018
except the Imam himself.

351
00:12:17.148 --> 00:12:18.454
And is that normal?

352
00:12:18.584 --> 00:12:20.369
No.

353
00:12:20.499 --> 00:12:22.980
And Yasmeen didn't seem to care.

354
00:12:23.111 --> 00:12:26.592
She even took private meetings
in his office with him.

355
00:12:26.723 --> 00:12:29.204
And now that she's missing.
he's not even concerned.

356
00:12:29.334 --> 00:12:30.945
like he never even knew her.

357
00:12:31.075 --> 00:12:33.904
How long has your sister
known this Imam?

358
00:12:34.035 --> 00:12:38.213
He came from Dearborn
four months ago.

359
00:12:38.343 --> 00:12:39.344
Everyone seems to like him.

360
00:12:39.475 --> 00:12:43.174
but something's not right.

361
00:12:43.305 --> 00:12:44.654
Please.

362
00:12:44.785 --> 00:12:47.483
whatever happened to my sister.

363
00:12:47.613 --> 00:12:50.616
we just want to know.

364
00:12:50.747 --> 00:12:52.401
- I appreciate it.
Hey. guys.

365
00:12:52.531 --> 00:12:54.577
so the Imam just jumped
to the top of the board.

366
00:12:54.707 --> 00:12:56.013
JOC looked into his history
in Dearborn.

367
00:12:56.144 --> 00:12:57.667
and there is another
homicide investigation

368
00:12:57.798 --> 00:12:59.930
of a Muslim woman still open.

369
00:13:00.061 --> 00:13:01.192
Now. I'm still waiting
for the chief investigator

370
00:13:01.323 --> 00:13:02.628
to call me back.

371
00:13:02.759 --> 00:13:04.717
but Imam Aziz.
he fits the timeline.

372
00:13:04.848 --> 00:13:06.241
Sorry. OA.

373
00:13:06.371 --> 00:13:06.981
I know you don't want
to hear that.

374
00:13:07.111 --> 00:13:08.460
It's OK.

375
00:13:08.591 --> 00:13:09.287
If women are missing.
if people are dying.

376
00:13:09.418 --> 00:13:10.419
we got to get to
the bottom of it.

377
00:13:10.549 --> 00:13:12.160
It doesn't matter who he is.

378
00:13:12.290 --> 00:13:14.597
So you think the Imam came to
Brooklyn to escape accusations?

379
00:13:14.727 --> 00:13:16.033
It's possible.

380
00:13:16.164 --> 00:13:17.382
There's no central authority
that places Imams.

381
00:13:17.513 --> 00:13:18.688
They're freelancers.

382
00:13:18.819 --> 00:13:20.037
They go to whatever
mosque will pay.

383
00:13:20.168 --> 00:13:21.473
and mosques don't usually
talk to each other.

384
00:13:21.604 --> 00:13:23.040
especially from other states.

385
00:13:23.171 --> 00:13:24.955
So where do we start?

386
00:13:25.086 --> 00:13:27.697
Where he lives. the mosque.

387
00:13:27.828 --> 00:13:29.917
I-in order to get proof.
we're gonna have to go in.

388
00:13:30.047 --> 00:13:32.006
OK. well. there should be
an all-women's study group

389
00:13:32.136 --> 00:13:33.442
or a Halaqa.

390
00:13:33.572 --> 00:13:34.617
if we get someone in there.

391
00:13:34.747 --> 00:13:37.011
someone that can get close
to him.

392
00:13:37.141 --> 00:13:40.928
I think I've got our gal.

393
00:13:41.058 --> 00:13:43.365
Hey. you need help?

394
00:13:43.495 --> 00:13:45.106
I'm OK. thanks.

395
00:13:45.236 --> 00:13:47.673
I actually went through
a hijab phase in college.

396
00:13:47.804 --> 00:13:49.762
so muscle memory is still there.

397
00:13:49.893 --> 00:13:50.981
Zara Ushruf.

398
00:13:51.112 --> 00:13:52.983
OA Zidan. Nice to meet you.

399
00:13:53.114 --> 00:13:54.942
OA stands for?

400
00:13:55.072 --> 00:13:56.204
Omar Adom.

401
00:13:56.334 --> 00:13:58.206
Come on.

402
00:13:58.336 --> 00:14:00.643
You're telling me none of the
agents could pronounce Omar?

403
00:14:00.773 --> 00:14:02.036
Or are you just one
of those purists

404
00:14:02.166 --> 00:14:03.689
that doesn't want the "ein"
in your name butchered?

405
00:14:03.820 --> 00:14:05.343
No. it's just a nickname.

406
00:14:05.474 --> 00:14:06.649
Someone gave it to me
at the Bureau.

407
00:14:06.779 --> 00:14:09.173
It stuck faster
than I could blink.

408
00:14:09.304 --> 00:14:10.783
Um. you speak Arabic?

409
00:14:10.914 --> 00:14:12.350
Just. uh. what I remember
from Sunday school.

410
00:14:12.481 --> 00:14:14.657
a couple insults
and pick-up lines

411
00:14:14.787 --> 00:14:16.572
the MSA boys would use on me
in college.

412
00:14:16.702 --> 00:14:18.182
Any of them actually work?

413
00:14:18.313 --> 00:14:22.186
You're welcome to find out
at your own risk. Omar.

414
00:14:22.317 --> 00:14:24.101
My partner. Maggie Bell.

415
00:14:24.232 --> 00:14:26.103
- Hi.
- Hi. Zara.

416
00:14:26.234 --> 00:14:27.409
Nice to meet you.

417
00:14:27.539 --> 00:14:28.845
Jubal speaks highly of you.
- You as well.

418
00:14:28.976 --> 00:14:30.542
You running the play?
- Yes.

419
00:14:30.673 --> 00:14:32.283
The Imam is holding
a women's-only Halaqa

420
00:14:32.414 --> 00:14:34.503
in two hours.

421
00:14:34.633 --> 00:14:36.809
So the plan is we're gonna
send you in a little bit later.

422
00:14:36.940 --> 00:14:38.811
hopefully making you
an easy target.

423
00:14:38.942 --> 00:14:40.988
And then he'll invite you
for the one-on-one meeting.

424
00:14:41.118 --> 00:14:42.598
And while you are
distracting him.

425
00:14:42.728 --> 00:14:44.382
I will be inside
on a sneak-and-peek warrant

426
00:14:44.513 --> 00:14:45.644
in his office
and living quarters.

427
00:14:45.775 --> 00:14:46.776
seeing if I can find
any evidence

428
00:14:46.907 --> 00:14:48.299
that he actually abducted
these women.

429
00:14:48.430 --> 00:14:49.822
So I'm the bait?

430
00:14:49.953 --> 00:14:51.520
Well. I mean. federally trained.

431
00:14:51.650 --> 00:14:55.350
weapons-qualified bait.

432
00:14:55.480 --> 00:14:56.873
What do you think?

433
00:14:57.004 --> 00:14:58.788
Will he bite?

434
00:14:58.919 --> 00:14:59.832
Who wouldn't?

435
00:14:59.963 --> 00:15:02.748
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

436
00:15:02.879 --> 00:15:10.879
<i>♪</i>

437
00:15:17.676 --> 00:15:18.895
Approaching the mosque now.

438
00:15:19.026 --> 00:15:20.462
Looks like noon prayer
just ended.

439
00:15:20.592 --> 00:15:21.637
Halaqa should be starting soon.

440
00:15:21.767 --> 00:15:22.943
Zara's already inside.

441
00:15:23.073 --> 00:15:31.073
<i>♪</i>

442
00:15:34.998 --> 00:15:36.782
There's too many eyes
in here right now.

443
00:15:36.913 --> 00:15:38.393
I'm gonna wait a minute.
let it clear out

444
00:15:38.523 --> 00:15:39.916
before I head
to the Imam's office.

445
00:15:40.047 --> 00:15:41.613
Copy.

446
00:15:41.744 --> 00:15:43.006
I'll head over to the
Sisters section in a second.

447
00:15:43.137 --> 00:15:44.399
get eyes on the Halaqa.

448
00:15:44.529 --> 00:15:45.661
It's midday.

449
00:15:45.791 --> 00:15:47.141
and it's not even Friday.

450
00:15:47.271 --> 00:15:49.926
This is way more crowded
than I expected it to be.

451
00:15:50.057 --> 00:15:50.927
Omar?

452
00:15:51.058 --> 00:15:52.494
Habibi!

453
00:15:52.624 --> 00:15:54.017
Amou Hisham!

454
00:15:54.148 --> 00:15:57.847
[speaking Arabic]

455
00:15:57.978 --> 00:15:59.588
Good to see you in the masjid.

456
00:15:59.718 --> 00:16:01.198
<i>What brings you to Brooklyn?</i>

457
00:16:01.329 --> 00:16:02.460
<i>A cousin's friend
is moving to New York.</i>

458
00:16:02.591 --> 00:16:03.940
I told him I'd check out
the mosque.

459
00:16:04.071 --> 00:16:06.334
see if the Islamic school has
any openings for his kids.

460
00:16:06.464 --> 00:16:08.118
When he comes.
give him my number.

461
00:16:08.249 --> 00:16:09.815
I can show him around.

462
00:16:09.946 --> 00:16:11.426
Are you coming over
for Iftar on Saturday?

463
00:16:11.556 --> 00:16:14.124
- Uh. I'll try. Inshallah.
- Good.

464
00:16:14.255 --> 00:16:16.474
You should meet
my friend's daughter. Saher.

465
00:16:16.605 --> 00:16:18.476
<i>She just finished her
master's degree at Cornell.</i>

466
00:16:18.607 --> 00:16:19.521
<i>Cornell?</i>

467
00:16:19.651 --> 00:16:22.176
[speaking Arabic]

468
00:16:22.306 --> 00:16:23.438
Yeah. well.
I should check out the school.

469
00:16:23.568 --> 00:16:24.439
OK. Ma'Salaama. habib.

470
00:16:24.569 --> 00:16:28.138
Ma'Salaama.

471
00:16:28.269 --> 00:16:30.575
<i>Well. so much for being
inconspicuous. OA.</i>

472
00:16:30.706 --> 00:16:31.750
It's my uncle's friend.

473
00:16:31.881 --> 00:16:33.622
I had no idea he went here.

474
00:16:33.752 --> 00:16:34.579
Is that common
for your community.

475
00:16:34.710 --> 00:16:36.712
people trying to set you up?

476
00:16:36.842 --> 00:16:38.061
Yeah.

477
00:16:38.192 --> 00:16:43.327
Like. all the time.

478
00:16:43.458 --> 00:16:45.112
It is funny.

479
00:16:45.242 --> 00:16:48.071
They fear the hijab. yet all
their nuns wear hijabs too.

480
00:16:48.202 --> 00:16:49.681
[chuckles]

481
00:16:49.812 --> 00:16:51.509
Are you here for
the Halaqa. sister?

482
00:16:51.640 --> 00:16:53.424
Yes. Am I late?

483
00:16:53.555 --> 00:16:54.947
That's all right.

484
00:16:55.078 --> 00:16:56.340
We're used to people thinking
it's Desi Standard Time.

485
00:16:56.471 --> 00:16:59.474
[laughter]
Take a seat.

486
00:16:59.604 --> 00:17:01.519
Tell us your name
and where you're from.

487
00:17:01.650 --> 00:17:02.781
Uh. Zara.

488
00:17:02.912 --> 00:17:04.653
I'm just visiting from Dallas.

489
00:17:04.783 --> 00:17:06.133
Oh. that's wonderful.

490
00:17:06.263 --> 00:17:08.309
The Qalam Institute is
doing great things there.

491
00:17:08.439 --> 00:17:10.224
You ever see my brother. YQ?

492
00:17:10.354 --> 00:17:13.227
<i>[tense music]</i>

493
00:17:13.357 --> 00:17:16.143
<i>♪</i>

494
00:17:16.273 --> 00:17:19.711
Um...

495
00:17:19.842 --> 00:17:21.322
Zara. he means Yasir Qadhi.

496
00:17:21.452 --> 00:17:22.714
Yes.

497
00:17:22.845 --> 00:17:25.152
Uh. Yasir Qadhi
is an amazing speaker.

498
00:17:25.282 --> 00:17:28.242
He gave the Eid Khutbah
last year.

499
00:17:28.372 --> 00:17:31.027
We don't have any imams
quite as eloquent as Yasir.

500
00:17:31.158 --> 00:17:33.029
So you'll have to make do
with me.

501
00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:36.250
[gentle laughter]

502
00:17:36.380 --> 00:17:37.860
Well. we were just talking
about the prophet

503
00:17:37.990 --> 00:17:39.427
Sallah-Allahu-Alayhi-Wa-Sallam.

504
00:17:39.557 --> 00:17:41.211
OK. OA.

505
00:17:41.342 --> 00:17:43.431
<i>Zara's with the Imam now.
You're clear to go.</i>

506
00:17:43.561 --> 00:17:45.563
Copy.

507
00:17:45.694 --> 00:17:48.392
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

508
00:17:48.523 --> 00:17:56.523
<i>♪</i>

509
00:18:06.976 --> 00:18:08.586
I'm in.

510
00:18:08.717 --> 00:18:16.717
<i>♪</i>

511
00:18:25.125 --> 00:18:27.562
Some say Waraqah was
the first convert to Islam.

512
00:18:27.692 --> 00:18:30.826
Others say no. the Prophet's
wife. Khadija was the first.

513
00:18:30.956 --> 00:18:32.175
But I'm not gonna
get into all that.

514
00:18:32.306 --> 00:18:33.437
[laughter]

515
00:18:33.568 --> 00:18:35.396
What's important is
this frail old man

516
00:18:35.526 --> 00:18:37.180
knew what the blessings were

517
00:18:37.311 --> 00:18:40.140
because he knew the reward
would be worth it.

518
00:18:40.270 --> 00:18:47.147
<i>♪</i>

519
00:18:47.277 --> 00:18:48.452
Hang on.

520
00:18:48.583 --> 00:18:49.932
That's weird.

521
00:18:50.062 --> 00:18:50.802
His Quran's on
his reading stand.

522
00:18:50.933 --> 00:18:52.543
Mm. what's weird about that?

523
00:18:52.674 --> 00:18:54.371
Well. it's too high
for him to actually read it.

524
00:18:54.502 --> 00:18:55.590
It would either be on his desk.
where he could read it.

525
00:18:55.720 --> 00:18:58.462
or in the case. unless...

526
00:18:58.593 --> 00:19:02.597
<i>♪</i>

527
00:19:02.727 --> 00:19:04.033
Waraqah knew
hard times were ahead.

528
00:19:04.164 --> 00:19:05.339
and still he said.

529
00:19:05.469 --> 00:19:07.558
<i>"I wish I could struggle
by your side.</i>

530
00:19:07.689 --> 00:19:11.562
<i>O Muhammad."</i>

531
00:19:11.693 --> 00:19:14.086
I found a key.

532
00:19:14.217 --> 00:19:17.002
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

533
00:19:17.133 --> 00:19:19.570
<i>♪</i>

534
00:19:19.701 --> 00:19:21.181
Oh. my God.

535
00:19:21.311 --> 00:19:22.312
<i>♪</i>

536
00:19:22.443 --> 00:19:24.445
Maggie.

537
00:19:24.575 --> 00:19:26.969
the key unlocks a locked drawer
with two passports in it.

538
00:19:27.099 --> 00:19:31.060
Yasmeen Hakeem and Laila Dani.
our missing women.

539
00:19:31.191 --> 00:19:33.323
Why does he have their
passports in his office?

540
00:19:33.454 --> 00:19:35.630
<i>♪</i>

541
00:19:35.760 --> 00:19:36.979
That's not it.

542
00:19:37.109 --> 00:19:38.720
There's also a woman's shirt.

543
00:19:38.850 --> 00:19:40.678
It's bloodstained.

544
00:19:40.809 --> 00:19:43.855
Sisters. it's Ramadan.
so we're going to stop early.

545
00:19:43.986 --> 00:19:45.727
Let's pick this up next week.

546
00:19:45.857 --> 00:19:51.298
[speaking Arabic]

547
00:19:51.428 --> 00:19:52.821
Zara.

548
00:19:52.951 --> 00:19:53.909
<i>you need to run interference.</i>

549
00:19:54.039 --> 00:19:55.519
<i>OA's still in his office.</i>

550
00:19:55.650 --> 00:19:59.131
<i>♪</i>

551
00:19:59.262 --> 00:20:01.482
Imam Aziz. sorry.

552
00:20:01.612 --> 00:20:03.484
Yes. Sister Zara?

553
00:20:03.614 --> 00:20:05.964
I. um.

554
00:20:06.095 --> 00:20:09.359
I actually came here
looking for some advice.

555
00:20:09.490 --> 00:20:12.144
advice I didn't want
getting back to Dallas.

556
00:20:12.275 --> 00:20:13.842
[phone buzzes]

557
00:20:13.972 --> 00:20:15.626
I'm sure people come to you
with this concern all the time.

558
00:20:15.757 --> 00:20:18.368
[phone buzzing]
<i>But it's where I find myself.</i>

559
00:20:18.499 --> 00:20:20.457
Lately. when I pray. I...

560
00:20:20.588 --> 00:20:22.459
I find my mind wanders.

561
00:20:22.590 --> 00:20:24.635
like I'm on autopilot.

562
00:20:24.766 --> 00:20:26.289
I'm so sorry. Sister Zara.

563
00:20:26.420 --> 00:20:28.291
but we'll have to continue this
another time.

564
00:20:28.422 --> 00:20:29.814
Assalamu-Alaikum.

565
00:20:29.945 --> 00:20:31.425
If I could actually
have another moment.

566
00:20:31.555 --> 00:20:32.730
Soon. Inshallah.

567
00:20:32.861 --> 00:20:36.517
<i>♪</i>

568
00:20:36.647 --> 00:20:38.867
<i>OA. the Imam is headed
towards you right now.</i>

569
00:20:38.997 --> 00:20:40.347
<i>You... you can't leave.
You can't exit.</i>

570
00:20:40.477 --> 00:20:41.391
<i>He's gonna see you.</i>

571
00:20:41.522 --> 00:20:42.523
<i>You gotta hide in there.</i>

572
00:20:42.653 --> 00:20:44.264
Where?

573
00:20:44.394 --> 00:20:52.394
<i>♪</i>

574
00:21:02.456 --> 00:21:03.718
He grabbed his jacket.

575
00:21:03.848 --> 00:21:07.809
I think he's leaving the mosque.

576
00:21:07.939 --> 00:21:11.203
[phone buzzes]

577
00:21:11.334 --> 00:21:14.206
Guys. news just broke that
Dr. Khan's body was found.

578
00:21:14.337 --> 00:21:15.338
He's probably going
to eliminate evidence.

579
00:21:15.469 --> 00:21:16.383
We got to go.

580
00:21:16.513 --> 00:21:19.299
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

581
00:21:19.429 --> 00:21:27.429
<i>♪</i>

582
00:21:27.916 --> 00:21:29.439
I got him.

583
00:21:29.570 --> 00:21:35.880
<i>♪</i>

584
00:21:36.011 --> 00:21:37.839
Jubal. the Imam's
heading east on foot.

585
00:21:37.969 --> 00:21:39.144
He looks to be in a hurry.

586
00:21:39.275 --> 00:21:43.627
<i>♪</i>

587
00:21:43.758 --> 00:21:44.976
All right. let us know

588
00:21:45.107 --> 00:21:46.630
when the Imam closes in
on an address.

589
00:21:46.761 --> 00:21:54.761
<i>♪</i>

590
00:21:59.164 --> 00:22:00.949
Jubal. it's a brownstone.

591
00:22:01.079 --> 00:22:02.603
Looks like there's
a guard outside.

592
00:22:02.733 --> 00:22:04.126
<i>67 West.</i>

593
00:22:04.256 --> 00:22:05.475
67 West.

594
00:22:05.606 --> 00:22:08.217
67 West. pulling it up now.

595
00:22:08.348 --> 00:22:09.784
OK. one of the registered
occupants...

596
00:22:09.914 --> 00:22:11.481
- Yeah?
- Dr. Saima Kahn.

597
00:22:11.612 --> 00:22:14.441
What?

598
00:22:14.571 --> 00:22:18.923
That can't be a coincidence.

599
00:22:19.054 --> 00:22:20.621
He's going inside.

600
00:22:20.751 --> 00:22:23.101
So are we.

601
00:22:23.232 --> 00:22:24.233
FBI.

602
00:22:24.364 --> 00:22:26.322
Hands up. right now.
Hands up.

603
00:22:26.453 --> 00:22:27.758
Go down.

604
00:22:27.889 --> 00:22:29.978
Move. Hands behind your back.

605
00:22:30.108 --> 00:22:31.196
Keep your mouth shut.

606
00:22:31.327 --> 00:22:33.198
<i>♪</i>

607
00:22:33.329 --> 00:22:35.287
Let's go.

608
00:22:35.418 --> 00:22:36.332
FBI!

609
00:22:36.463 --> 00:22:37.507
Don't move.

610
00:22:37.638 --> 00:22:39.030
Show me your hands.

611
00:22:39.161 --> 00:22:40.597
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

612
00:22:40.728 --> 00:22:42.643
Who else is back there?

613
00:22:42.773 --> 00:22:44.166
Open the door.

614
00:22:44.296 --> 00:22:45.515
It's not what you think.

615
00:22:45.646 --> 00:22:46.908
Now!

616
00:22:47.038 --> 00:22:51.347
- Open it.
- Move.

617
00:22:51.478 --> 00:22:53.088
Please.
no one needs to get hurt.

618
00:22:53.218 --> 00:22:54.219
- You're OK.
You're OK.

619
00:22:54.350 --> 00:22:56.439
We're FBI.

620
00:22:56.570 --> 00:22:57.309
You guys are safe now.

621
00:22:57.440 --> 00:22:59.050
Jubal. we found Yasmeen. Laila.

622
00:22:59.181 --> 00:22:59.964
and there's a third woman.

623
00:23:00.095 --> 00:23:01.618
- [grunts]
- No!

624
00:23:01.749 --> 00:23:02.706
What are you doing to him?

625
00:23:02.837 --> 00:23:03.707
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.

626
00:23:03.838 --> 00:23:04.969
The Imam is keeping us safe.

627
00:23:05.100 --> 00:23:06.275
He's protecting us.

628
00:23:06.406 --> 00:23:07.755
Protecting you?

629
00:23:07.885 --> 00:23:08.886
From who?

630
00:23:09.017 --> 00:23:11.411
<i>♪</i>

631
00:23:17.068 --> 00:23:18.374
Yasmeen.

632
00:23:18.505 --> 00:23:20.420
we're all relieved that you
and the other women

633
00:23:20.550 --> 00:23:22.247
were found alive and safe.

634
00:23:22.378 --> 00:23:25.381
But we do have a few questions
we need to ask you.

635
00:23:25.512 --> 00:23:28.776
Now. you said that the Imam
was helping keep you safe.

636
00:23:28.906 --> 00:23:31.561
From who?

637
00:23:31.692 --> 00:23:34.129
Our husbands.

638
00:23:34.259 --> 00:23:36.044
I'm sorry. Amani.

639
00:23:36.174 --> 00:23:38.089
There were rules
we had to follow.

640
00:23:38.220 --> 00:23:41.571
I couldn't tell anyone I was
leaving him. not even you.

641
00:23:41.702 --> 00:23:43.573
Yasmeen.

642
00:23:43.704 --> 00:23:45.749
your husband.

643
00:23:45.880 --> 00:23:47.577
was he violent?

644
00:23:47.708 --> 00:23:52.147
Not at first.

645
00:23:52.277 --> 00:23:54.236
Khaled controlled all our money.

646
00:23:54.366 --> 00:23:57.282
told me where
I was allowed to go.

647
00:23:57.413 --> 00:24:00.503
If I disobeyed him.

648
00:24:00.634 --> 00:24:03.419
he got so angry.

649
00:24:03.550 --> 00:24:06.422
It went on for years.

650
00:24:06.553 --> 00:24:09.251
Then a few weeks ago.

651
00:24:09.381 --> 00:24:11.209
it got worse.

652
00:24:11.340 --> 00:24:14.343
He hit you?

653
00:24:14.474 --> 00:24:18.869
Oh. Yasmeen. I am so sorry.

654
00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:22.264
Yasmeen.
the reason that we're asking

655
00:24:22.394 --> 00:24:26.224
is that Dr. Khan was found
murdered this morning.

656
00:24:26.355 --> 00:24:27.965
What?

657
00:24:28.096 --> 00:24:29.401
No.

658
00:24:29.532 --> 00:24:30.925
No.

659
00:24:31.055 --> 00:24:34.537
Was she helping Imam Aziz
keep you guys

660
00:24:34.668 --> 00:24:35.756
hidden in the house?

661
00:24:35.886 --> 00:24:38.149
Her... her name was on the lease.

662
00:24:38.280 --> 00:24:41.152
And you want to know if my
husband could have killed her?

663
00:24:41.283 --> 00:24:44.112
<i>[tense music]</i>

664
00:24:44.242 --> 00:24:46.549
<i>♪</i>

665
00:24:46.680 --> 00:24:47.985
Yes.

666
00:24:48.116 --> 00:24:54.688
<i>♪</i>

667
00:24:54.818 --> 00:24:57.168
- Am I in trouble?
- No. No.

668
00:24:57.299 --> 00:25:01.216
I just wanted us to have
a private place to speak.

669
00:25:01.346 --> 00:25:02.739
I was hoping you could tell me

670
00:25:02.870 --> 00:25:05.176
how you ended up
in the safe house.

671
00:25:05.307 --> 00:25:06.613
I'm good.

672
00:25:06.743 --> 00:25:08.484
Thanks.

673
00:25:08.615 --> 00:25:10.312
Maybe you feel like
I won't be able to understand

674
00:25:10.442 --> 00:25:13.141
your situation.

675
00:25:13.271 --> 00:25:14.185
Try me.

676
00:25:14.316 --> 00:25:17.058
My situation is my business.

677
00:25:17.188 --> 00:25:19.364
It's a little
more complicated now.

678
00:25:19.495 --> 00:25:22.498
We're trying to figure out
who killed Dr. Kahn.

679
00:25:22.629 --> 00:25:24.108
And I know that
all those other women

680
00:25:24.239 --> 00:25:25.588
who were in that safe house
had husbands

681
00:25:25.719 --> 00:25:26.937
that they were hiding from.

682
00:25:27.068 --> 00:25:30.637
But you're not married.

683
00:25:30.767 --> 00:25:36.033
Aaliyah.
who are you hiding from?

684
00:25:36.164 --> 00:25:40.168
Is it possible that that person
could have murdered Dr. Khan?

685
00:25:40.298 --> 00:25:41.517
I'd like to leave now.

686
00:25:41.648 --> 00:25:43.258
OK. Aaliyah. please.

687
00:25:43.388 --> 00:25:44.694
I'm really sorry about
what happened to her.

688
00:25:44.825 --> 00:25:49.351
But I can't help you.

689
00:25:49.481 --> 00:25:51.788
May I go now?

690
00:25:51.919 --> 00:25:54.704
The only place
Khaled would let me go.

691
00:25:54.835 --> 00:25:57.533
no questions asked.
was the mosque.

692
00:25:57.664 --> 00:26:01.668
So one day. I showed up late
with my nose broken.

693
00:26:01.798 --> 00:26:04.366
my shirt still soaked
with blood.

694
00:26:04.496 --> 00:26:06.281
The same shirt that we found
in his private office?

695
00:26:06.411 --> 00:26:07.456
Yes.

696
00:26:07.587 --> 00:26:08.936
He asked to keep it as evidence

697
00:26:09.066 --> 00:26:10.677
in case I decided
to press charges.

698
00:26:10.807 --> 00:26:13.549
But I just wanted out.

699
00:26:13.680 --> 00:26:15.246
And Imam Aziz promised to help.

700
00:26:15.377 --> 00:26:17.292
And that's why
he had your passport.

701
00:26:17.422 --> 00:26:20.861
Passport?

702
00:26:20.991 --> 00:26:22.689
You were going to leave us?

703
00:26:22.819 --> 00:26:25.430
There were no good options.

704
00:26:25.561 --> 00:26:27.955
In these situations.
there never really are.

705
00:26:28.085 --> 00:26:31.828
I suppose now. you think it's
typical of a Muslim community.

706
00:26:31.959 --> 00:26:34.048
No. actually. I don't.

707
00:26:34.178 --> 00:26:36.267
because I've seen it myself.

708
00:26:36.398 --> 00:26:38.095
in every community.

709
00:26:38.226 --> 00:26:41.011
<i>♪</i>

710
00:26:41.142 --> 00:26:43.666
If my husband did this.

711
00:26:43.797 --> 00:26:47.235
you have to stop him.

712
00:26:47.365 --> 00:26:48.889
Maggie just finished
her interviews

713
00:26:49.019 --> 00:26:50.281
with the last of the women
we found.

714
00:26:50.412 --> 00:26:51.326
The Imam's definitely
not our killer.

715
00:26:51.456 --> 00:26:52.632
Yeah. I know.

716
00:26:52.762 --> 00:26:53.633
The Dearborn police chief
just reached out.

717
00:26:53.763 --> 00:26:55.025
That homicide
from four months ago.

718
00:26:55.156 --> 00:26:56.679
they're looking into
the husbands now.

719
00:26:56.810 --> 00:26:59.334
We did the best we could
with the information we had.

720
00:26:59.464 --> 00:27:01.684
My gut just told me
something was off.

721
00:27:01.815 --> 00:27:03.425
and I should have
listened to it.

722
00:27:03.555 --> 00:27:06.384
Your gut is also
very hungry right now.

723
00:27:06.515 --> 00:27:08.125
It's the coffee I miss the most.

724
00:27:08.256 --> 00:27:09.736
Well. you can't have a coffee

725
00:27:09.866 --> 00:27:11.172
without an egg and cheese
on a roll.

726
00:27:11.302 --> 00:27:14.523
buttered on both sides.
extra hot sauce.

727
00:27:14.654 --> 00:27:16.873
ketchup oozing out of the back
with every bite.

728
00:27:17.004 --> 00:27:19.093
- You're a...
you're a monster. Zara.

729
00:27:19.223 --> 00:27:20.311
You've been out of the game.

730
00:27:20.442 --> 00:27:22.009
You just started fasting again.

731
00:27:22.139 --> 00:27:23.575
And how on Earth
can you tell that?

732
00:27:23.706 --> 00:27:27.449
- I'm not a monster.
I'm just observant.

733
00:27:27.579 --> 00:27:29.494
We're gonna get justice
for Dr. Khan.

734
00:27:29.625 --> 00:27:31.496
We just have to build on
what we have.

735
00:27:31.627 --> 00:27:34.412
We know that she was helping
the Imam keep the women safe.

736
00:27:34.543 --> 00:27:36.632
The killer has to be
one of their husbands.

737
00:27:36.763 --> 00:27:38.286
Well. the JOC is looking
into their alibis.

738
00:27:38.416 --> 00:27:39.635
and NYPD is being looped into

739
00:27:39.766 --> 00:27:41.289
dropped spousal abuse charges.
but...

740
00:27:41.419 --> 00:27:46.424
Something's still bothering you?

741
00:27:46.555 --> 00:27:48.992
The third woman. Aaliyah Idris.

742
00:27:49.123 --> 00:27:50.385
She doesn't match the pattern.

743
00:27:50.515 --> 00:27:51.734
Not married.

744
00:27:51.865 --> 00:27:52.953
Or declared missing.

745
00:27:53.083 --> 00:27:54.563
Maggie did say
when she asked her

746
00:27:54.694 --> 00:27:56.434
who she was hiding from.
she clammed up.

747
00:27:56.565 --> 00:27:59.960
<i>[tense music]</i>

748
00:28:00.090 --> 00:28:02.310
OK. so what if the reason
that Aaliyah Idris was hiding

749
00:28:02.440 --> 00:28:04.268
in the safe house
is the same reason

750
00:28:04.399 --> 00:28:06.749
why Dr. Khan was murdered?

751
00:28:06.880 --> 00:28:07.881
We have to press her.

752
00:28:08.011 --> 00:28:11.101
<i>♪</i>

753
00:28:11.232 --> 00:28:14.322
Maggie.
did you release Aaliyah yet?

754
00:28:14.452 --> 00:28:15.584
Aaliyah?

755
00:28:15.715 --> 00:28:16.803
Aaliyah. hang on.

756
00:28:16.933 --> 00:28:18.282
We're on your side.

757
00:28:18.413 --> 00:28:20.154
Keep telling yourself that.

758
00:28:20.284 --> 00:28:22.199
You were in the safe house
for a reason.

759
00:28:22.330 --> 00:28:24.288
You're running from
something or someone.

760
00:28:24.419 --> 00:28:26.116
Dr. Khan was protecting you.

761
00:28:26.247 --> 00:28:27.770
and it probably cost her
her life.

762
00:28:27.901 --> 00:28:29.511
You could die.

763
00:28:29.641 --> 00:28:31.034
You are safe with us.

764
00:28:31.165 --> 00:28:33.210
but if you leave our custody.
we cannot protect you.

765
00:28:33.341 --> 00:28:34.864
You think
the FBI can protect me?

766
00:28:34.995 --> 00:28:36.170
I do.

767
00:28:36.300 --> 00:28:37.606
This is what we're trained for.

768
00:28:37.737 --> 00:28:38.868
Aaliyah. let us help you.

769
00:28:38.999 --> 00:28:41.653
<i>♪</i>

770
00:28:41.784 --> 00:28:43.786
You want to stop me?

771
00:28:43.917 --> 00:28:46.006
Then you'll have to arrest me.

772
00:28:46.136 --> 00:28:49.879
<i>♪</i>

773
00:28:50.010 --> 00:28:51.751
All right then.

774
00:28:51.881 --> 00:28:57.234
<i>♪</i>

775
00:28:57.365 --> 00:28:59.323
OK. she wants to take
her chances without us.

776
00:28:59.454 --> 00:29:00.977
It's suicide.

777
00:29:01.108 --> 00:29:02.936
I'm gonna call the JOC and
get some surveillance on her.

778
00:29:03.066 --> 00:29:04.546
We need to figure out
who she's running from.

779
